Adjust racks to middle and top positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Trim and halve @Brussels sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise. Lay flat and thinly slice crosswise into shreds.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon}, half the @ranch spice{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on middle rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, half the @Parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon}, half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, remaining ranch spice, a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper.

Lightly oil a second baking sheet. Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season with salt and pepper.

Place chicken on prepared sheet. Evenly brush tops with a thin layer of @Caesar dressing{1.5%ounce} (save the rest for serving). Mound coated sides with panko mixture, pressing to adhere (no need to coat the undersides). Roast chicken on top rack for ~{10%minutes} (you'll finish the chicken in step 5).

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add Brussels sprouts and cook, stirring occasionally, until bright green and softened, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season with remaining garlic powder, salt, and pepper.

Remove pan from heat.

Once chicken has roasted 10 minutes, remove sheet from oven. Carefully sprinkle remaining Parmesan over chicken.

Return to top rack until chicken is browned and cooked through and Parmesan is golden brown, ~{6-10%minutes} more.

Divide chicken, Brussels sprouts, and potato wedges between plates. Drizzle remaining dressing over chicken (or serve on the side for dipping).

> Keep a close eye on the cheese to avoid burning.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165º.